#. Tag: title
#: faq.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Questions and Answers"
msgstr "Vprašanja in odgovori"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid "How dangerous is &partman; for my data?"
msgstr "Kako nevaren je &partman; za moje podatke?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First of all, you should never perform any destructive operations (delete, "
"move, resize) without first making a complete backup of everything affected."
msgstr ""
"Prvič, nikoli ne izvajajte nobenih destruktivnih operacij (brisanje, "
"premikanje, spreminjanje velikosti), ne da bi prej naredili popolno "
"varnostno kopijo vsega, kar je prizadeto."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Having said that, &partman; is safe to use. It performs extensive checks "
"before and after every operation. It calls external tools written and "
"supported by the file system authors. And it has been tested extensively."
msgstr ""
"Ob tem je &partman; varen za uporabo. Izvaja obsežne preglede pred in po "
"vsaki operaciji. Prikliče zunanja orodja, ki so jih napisali in podprli "
"avtorji datotečnega sistema. In to je bilo obsežno testirano."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is always the risk of data loss due to an unknown bug. &partman;'s "
"authors try to minimize this risk, but there are of course no guarantees."
msgstr ""
"Vedno obstaja nevarnost izgube podatkov zaradi neznane napake. Avtorji "
"&partman; poskušajo zmanjšati to tveganje, vendar seveda ni nobenih "
"zagotovil."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I have installed all recommended external file system support packages and "
"still do not get support for all operations on all file systems."
msgstr ""
"Namestil sem vse priporočene podporne pakete za zunanji datotečni sistem in "
"še vedno ne dobim podpore za vse operacije v vseh datotečnih sistemih."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Not everything &partman; can do in principle can be done with all file "
"systems."
msgstr "&partman; načeloma ne more narediti vsega z vsemi datotečnimi sistemi."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One example is performing a file system check on linuxswap: It is just not "
"possible. There are other limitations like that inherent in some file "
"systems. You cannot shrink JFS or XFS file systems because neither of the "
"two supports shrinking at all, with or without &partman;."
msgstr ""
"En primer je izvajanje preverjanja datotečnega sistema na linuxswap: to "
"preprosto ni mogoče. Obstajajo tudi druge omejitve, podobne tistim, ki so "
"del nekaterih datotečnih sistemov. Datotečnih sistemov JFS ali XFS ne morete "
"skrčiti, ker nobeden od obeh sploh ne podpira krčenja, z ali brez &partman;."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why can't I see any meaningful progress information when resizing a "
"partition?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj pri spreminjanju velikosti particije ne vidim nobenih pomembnih "
"informacij o napredku?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&partman; can only show progress information when it knows how long the jobs "
"in an operation will take. Unfortunately this is usually not the case when "
"resizing partitions because the by far longest job when doing so is resizing "
"the file system on the partition. Resizing file systems is in most cases "
"something an external tool will do on behalf of &partman; and these external "
"tools do not provide useful progress information to &partman;, so there's "
"nothing to report while they are running."
msgstr ""
"&partman; lahko prikaže informacije o napredku le, če ve, kako dolgo bodo "
"opravila v operaciji trajala. Na žalost to običajno ne velja pri "
"spreminjanju velikosti particij, ker je daleč najdaljše delo pri tem "
"spreminjanje velikosti datotečnega sistema na particiji. Spreminjanje "
"velikosti datotečnih sistemov je v večini primerov nekaj, kar bo zunanje "
"orodje naredilo v imenu &partman; in ta zunanja orodja &partman; ne nudijo "
"uporabnih informacij o napredku, zato med izvajanjem ni kaj poročati."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why can't I resize the root partition? How can I resize the partition /home "
"is on?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj ne morem spremeniti velikosti korenske particije? Kako lahko spremenim "
"velikost priklopljene particije /home?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To modify a partition it must not be mounted. You can however not unmount "
"the root partition. Neither will you be able to unmount the home partition "
"if the home directory of the currently logged in user is on it."
msgstr ""
"Če želite spremeniti particijo, ne sme biti priklopljena. Vendar korenske "
"particije ne morete odklopiti. Prav tako ne boste mogli odklopiti particije /"
"home, če je na tem domačem imeniku trenutno prijavljen uporabnik."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The solution for this problem is to boot from a Linux Live CD that comes "
"with &partman; and modify these partitions from there."
msgstr ""
"Rešitev za to težavo je zagon s CD-ja Linux Live, ki mu je priložen "
"&partman; in od tam spremenite te particije."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I'm getting a warning message in the log output about something that a "
"partition cannot be created with the size I requested and that it will "
"instead be smaller. What happened?"
msgstr ""
"V izpisu dnevnika prejemam opozorilno sporočilo o nečem, da particije ni "
"mogoče ustvariti z velikostjo, ki sem jo zahteval, in da bo namesto tega "
"manjša. Kaj se je zgodilo?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On MS-DOS partition tables, partitions have to begin and end on cylinder "
"boundaries. This is mainly for historical reasons. &partman; will deal with "
"this internally and try not to bother the user with that limitation."
msgstr ""
"V particijskih tabelah MS-DOS se morajo particije začeti in končati na mejah "
"valja. To je predvsem zaradi zgodovinskih razlogov. &partman; se bo s tem "
"ukvarjal interno in poskušal uporabnika ne motiti s to omejitvijo."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Under rare circumstances, &partman; will however not be able to set up an "
"operation in the way the user requested it due to this limitation. For "
"example, if one cylinder on a device is 8 MiB large and you try to resize a "
"partition by 6 MiB, this will not work."
msgstr ""
"V redkih okoliščinah &partman; zaradi te omejitve ne bo mogel nastaviti "
"operacije na način, ki ga je zahteval uporabnik. Na primer, če je en valj v "
"napravi velik 8 MiB in poskušate spremeniti velikost particije za 6 MiB, to "
"ne bo delovalo."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You might also encounter this message if you have a device and partition "
"table where the partitions are, for whatever reason, not correctly snapped "
"to cylinder boundaries and you try to move or copy these partitions for the "
"first time."
msgstr ""
"Na to sporočilo lahko naletite tudi, če imate tabelo naprav in particij, "
"kjer particije iz kakršnega koli razloga niso pravilno pritrjene na meje "
"valja in poskušate te particije premakniti ali kopirati prvič."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The message itself is harmless and only exists to inform the user that "
"something can not be done quite exactly the way the user expects. Your "
"partitions and data will not be negatively affected in any way if you see "
"this message."
msgstr ""
"Sporočilo samo po sebi je neškodljivo in obstaja samo zato, da obvesti "
"uporabnika, da nekaj ni mogoče narediti čisto tako, kot uporabnik pričakuje. "
"Če vidite to sporočilo, to ne bo negativno vplivalo na vaše particije in "
"podatke."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "How many operations can I add to the list of pending operations?"
msgstr "Koliko operacij lahko dodam na seznam čakajočih operacij?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "There is no limit."
msgstr "Omejitev ni."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is however not recommended to add too many operations to the list. There "
"is always a small chance an operation might fail with an error, in which "
"case &partman; will stop executing operations. In that case it is a lot "
"easier to find out what happened (and to re-add all the operations that "
"could not be executed) if the list of pending operations was not exceedingly "
"long."
msgstr ""
"Vendar ni priporočljivo dodajati preveč operacij na seznam. Vedno obstaja "
"majhna možnost, da operacija ne uspe z napako, v tem primeru &partman; bo "
"prenehal z izvajanjem operacij. V tem primeru je veliko lažje ugotoviti, kaj "
"se je zgodilo (in ponovno dodati vse operacije, ki jih ni bilo mogoče "
"izvesti), če seznam čakajočih operacij ni bil pretirano dolg."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Resizing an ext2 or ext3 file system failed with something in the report "
"about <quote>no space left on device</quote>. What happened? Is my data "
"corrupted now?"
msgstr ""
"Spreminjanje velikosti datotečnega sistema ext2 ali ext3 ni uspelo z nekaj v "
"poročilu o <quote>ni prostora v napravi</quote>. Kaj se je zgodilo? Ali so "
"moji podatki zdaj poškodovani?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is a problem of the <command>e2resize</command> command and the "
"underlying ext2/3/4 file system. If a file system is nearly full, "
"<command>e2resize</command> cannot make it any smaller even though that "
"should be possible from the number of free sectors left. &partman; can "
"unfortunately not know beforehand if <command>e2resize</command> will abort "
"with this error for a given file system or not. If it happens, nothing will "
"be done at all and your data will not be negatively affected."
msgstr ""
"To je težava ukaza <command>e2resize</command> in osnovnega datotečnega "
"sistema ext2/3/4. Če je datotečni sistem skoraj poln, ga <command>e2resize</"
"command> ne more zmanjšati, čeprav bi to moralo biti mogoče glede na število "
"preostalih prostih sektorjev. &partman; na žalost ne more vnaprej vedeti, "
"ali se bo <command>e2resize</command> prekinil s to napako za dani datotečni "
"sistem ali ne. Če se to zgodi, ne bo storjeno nič in na vaše podatki ne bo "
"negativnega vpliva."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "There is no real workaround for this problem right now."
msgstr "Za to težavo trenutno ni prave rešitve."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why can't I format my floppy disk with &partman;? Why is there no support "
"for CD writing or DVD burning?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj ne morem formatirati svoje diskete z &partman;? Zakaj ni podpore za "
"zapisovanje CD-jev ali DVD-jev?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"None of this is what &partman; has been designed to do: It is an application "
"that deals with partitions and the file systems on these partitions. Floppy "
"disks, CDs or DVDs do not need or use partitions."
msgstr ""
"Nič od tega ni tisto, zaradi lesa je bil zasnovan &partman;: Je aplikacija, "
"ki se ukvarja s particijami in datotečnimi sistemi na teh particijah. "
"Diskete, CD-ji ali DVD-ji ne potrebujejo ali uporabljajo particij."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why can't I modify partitions on a device with an amiga or bsd partition "
"table?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj ne morem spreminjati particij na napravi s particijsko tabelo amiga "
"ali bsd?"

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&partman; currently only allows read-only access to any other partition "
"table type than MS-DOS. This is for safety reasons: Support in &partman; for "
"this partition table types is not really there and what is there (or just "
"incidentally works) has not been tested enough to use it with confidence."
msgstr ""
"&partman; trenutno dovoljuje le dostop samo za branje do katere koli druge "
"vrste particijske tabele razen MS-DOS. To je zaradi varnosti: Podpora v "
"&partman; za te vrste particijskih tabel v resnici ni in tisto, kar obstaja "
"(ali samo mimogrede deluje), ni bilo dovolj preizkušeno, da bi to lahko "
"zanesljivo uporabljali."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Of course you can still create a new MS-DOS partition table on the device in "
"question, but that is probably not what you want."
msgstr ""
"Seveda lahko še vedno ustvarite novo particijsko tabelo MS-DOS na zadevni "
"napravi, vendar to verjetno ni tisto, kar želite."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On startup, &partman; hangs for a couple of minutes while it apparently "
"tries to scan the floppy drive on my computer."
msgstr ""
"Ob zagonu &partman; visi za nekaj minut, medtem ko očitno poskuša pregledati "
"disketni pogon v mojem računalniku."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This happens if you have a floppy drive configured in your computer's BIOS "
"settings but have not actually connected one. If you do not have a floppy "
"drive check your BIOS settings and disable any floppy drives configured "
"there to see if this makes the problem go away."
msgstr ""
"To se zgodi, če imate v nastavitvah BIOS-a računalnika konfiguriran disketni "
"pogon, vendar ga dejansko niste priključili. Če nimate disketnega pogona, "
"preverite nastavitve BIOS-a in onemogočite vse tam konfigurirane disketne "
"pogone, da vidite, ali bo s tem težava izginila."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During startup, &partman; prints some message about probing devices and that "
"it might even crash or at least take a long time."
msgstr ""
"Med zagonom &partman; natisne neko sporočilo o napravah za sondiranje in da "
"se lahko celo zruši ali vsaj dolgo traja."

#. Tag: para
#: faq.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LibParted, a backend library &partman; uses, has problems with systems where "
"the Linux Device Mapper is used in a way it doesn't understand. "
"Unfortunately it reacts to some of these situations with segmentation "
"faults, i.e. crashes. &partman; therefore tries to avoid these situations by "
"using an alternative way to scan your computer for disks. If it cannot do "
"that, however, and therefore has to rely on LibParted, it will print a "
"message like the one mentioned. If the scanning for disks works, you can "
"safely disregard the message."
msgstr ""
"LibParted, zaledna knjižnica, ki jo uporablja &partman;, ima težave s "
"sistemi, kjer se program Linux Device Mapper uporablja na način, ki ga ne "
"razume. Na žalost se na nekatere od teh situacij odzove z napakami v "
"segmentaciji, tj. sesutji. &partman; se zato skuša izogniti tem situacijam z "
"uporabo alternativnega načina prečesavanja vašega računalnika za diski. Če "
"tega ne more storiti in se mora zato zanesti na LibParted, bo natisnil "
"sporočilo, kot je omenjeno. Če iskanje diskov deluje, lahko mirno prezrete "
"sporočilo."
